<item>
            <title>[TIKA-3575] Cannot use loadErrorHandler=&quot;ignore&quot; in tika config</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3575</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tika 2.0.0 changed the default error handler to throw exceptions, and does not ignore errors when loading parsers anymore as it was the case with Tika 1.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See  &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/e47c6cd62e587fdaae7e2e999f37122d09449754#diff-3955d56f4d95c6e600966c486c58f92483c900d32d553d18b3cf2940cbf2c768R470&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/e47c6cd62e587fdaae7e2e999f37122d09449754#diff-3955d56f4d95c6e600966c486c58f92483c900d32d553d18b3cf2940cbf2c768R470&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s no configuration option to restore the previous behavior. It should be possible to set&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;service-loader loadErrorHandler=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ignore&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but the code in org.apache.tika.config.TikaConfig#serviceLoaderFromDomElement only considers &quot;warn&quot; and &quot;throw&quot; as possible values.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
